    <a title="Artemiz" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/7534408-artemiz"><img alt="Artemiz" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1327579998p2/7534408.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/964123432?book_show_action=true">Jun 11, 2014</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Artemiz" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Artemiz" href="/user/show/7534408-artemiz">Artemiz</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/7534408-artemiz?shelf=netgalley">netgalley</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/7534408-artemiz?shelf=2014">2014</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer964123432" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer6153612733733072936">Border Lord by Arnette Lamb is a good romance story. It&apos;s no bodice ripper story. There is a strong (read: head strong :)) heroine and strong (read: tricky, loyal and loving) hero.<br/><br/>There is no swooning, no sulking, no storming off in this book. There are two educated adults who a playing a complicated game of chess without even realizing it. The stakes at this game are high and one wrong move can bring devastation to either one of them. When they realize the stakes, it might be already to late, b</span>
  <span id="freeText6153612733733072936" style="display:none">Border Lord by Arnette Lamb is a good romance story. It's no bodice ripper story. There is a strong (read: head strong :)) heroine and strong (read: tricky, loyal and loving) hero.<br /><br />There is no swooning, no sulking, no storming off in this book. There are two educated adults who a playing a complicated game of chess without even realizing it. The stakes at this game are high and one wrong move can bring devastation to either one of them. When they realize the stakes, it might be already to late, but it wouldn't be a romance novel, if the ending would not be happy. So our leading lady and lord dance their complicated dance, show their cards little by little and at the end they find the ending that is satisfying to all the parties involved. <br /><br />It's a good book!</span>
  <a data-text-id="6153612733733072936" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


